Class LoadtestInlineScriptContext

    • Field Detail

      • CONTEXT_SCOPE_GLOBAL

        public static final int CONTEXT_SCOPE_GLOBAL
        The context contains only global information about the load test. This context type is typical for inline scripts which are executed at global level (before or after a load test). Value = 1.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • CONTEXT_SCOPE_USER

        public static final int CONTEXT_SCOPE_USER
        The context contains global information and per user specific information. This context type is typical for inline scripts which are executed at user level (before a user is created or after a user has been completed). Value = 2.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • CONTEXT_SCOPE_LOOP

        public static final int CONTEXT_SCOPE_LOOP
        The context contains global information, per user specific information and per executed loop specific information. This context type is typical for inline scripts which are executed at loop level (before a loop has been started or after a loop has been completed). and for inline scripts which are bound to an item inside the loop (for example a page break). Value = 3.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • CONTEXT_SCOPE_URL

        public static final int CONTEXT_SCOPE_URL
        The context contains global information, per user specific information, per executed loop specific information and specific information about the current URL call. This context type is typical for inline scripts which are executed at URL level (before a URL has been called or after a URL has been called). Value = 4.

        Note: inline scripts which are constructed and executed at loop level will receive an upgrade of the context in case when a loop has been failed form CONTEXT_SCOPE_LOOP to CONTEXT_SCOPE_URL.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • RESULT_TYPE_SET_OUTPUT_VARS

        public static final int RESULT_TYPE_SET_OUTPUT_VARS
        The inline script has to return a list of output vars. Note that this list can also be empty.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • RESULT_TYPE_IS_BOOLEAN

        public static final int RESULT_TYPE_IS_BOOLEAN
        The inline script has to return only one output var which must have the vale of either "0", or "1", or "false", or "true" Note that the return value is interpreted by the load test program as an boolean value.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • setUrlCallPassed

        public void setUrlCallPassed(boolean urlCallPassed)
        Set a flag that signals if a 'yellow' error did occur after the URL call (triggered by response verification settings). Note that this method is called only by the Java load test program (read-only inside inline-scripts).
        Parameters:
        urlCallPassed - false = a 'yellow' error did occur after the URL call, true = no 'yellow' error occurred (successful URL call)
        See Also:
        CONTEXT_SCOPE_URL, ProxySnifferVarSourceInlineScript.EXEC_SCOPE_URL_END, ProxySnifferVarSourceInlineScript.EXEC_SCOPE_ALL_URLS_END

      • setScriptAbort

        public void setScriptAbort(java.lang.String message)
        Mark the inline script as aborted. Depending on the context scope, the whole load test will be aborted (global), or the current user will be aborted (user), or the loop will be aborted (loop or url). Note: This method is called only by the script interpreter.
        Parameters:
        message - the reason why the inline script has aborted the execution.
        See Also:
        CONTEXT_SCOPE_GLOBAL, CONTEXT_SCOPE_USER, CONTEXT_SCOPE_LOOP, CONTEXT_SCOPE_URL
